Anglo American Platinum expects its annual earnings to shoot up by more than half due to higher prices. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Anglo American Platinum expects its annual earnings to shoot up by more than half due to higher prices. This is the second large Platinum Group Metals company to alert investors of strong growth in annual profits despite the CCOVID-19 pandemic disrupting operations. READ: Amplats CEO steps down Amplats says the sharp expected increase is driven by a 71 percent increase in the rand basket price. Last Friday, Sibanye-Stillwater said it would report a full-year attributable profit of up to R30-billion for its 2020 financial year. This from a R62-million profit the year before.